        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 4:51PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 451 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Beckville, or 12 miles north of Carthage, moving
southwest at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Carthage, Tatum and Beckville.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
